{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7961", "repo": "rails", "body": "I do see the the argument of keeping with AR's naming convention, but in this case: I would argue that `seconds_to_midnight` clearly would not return the number of seconds from any past midnight, but exactly the number of seconds until the next midnight. \r\n\r\nBut, this is semantics, and I just wanted to know, what the naming reasons was. Let's not argue about this :) :+1:", "_id": {"$oid": "523dbb41bd354364b900977b"}, "issue_id": 7961, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9487387", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7961#issuecomment-9487387", "updated_at": "2012-10-16T13:30:21Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekampp/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekampp/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekampp/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekampp/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekampp", "login": "ekampp", "gravatar_id": "798f66c6c7e53703e2a30ff911b0e884", "html_url": "https://github.com/ekampp", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekampp/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekampp/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekampp/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/798f66c6c7e53703e2a30ff911b0e884?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F9874e7748b87210dab60a15f1757d02f.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekampp/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 40206, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekampp/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-10-16T13:30:21Z", "id": 9487387, "owner": "rails"}
